{
  "texts": [
    "While adult learning theory helps explain how teachers learn and grow, the TPACK framework provides a more specific framework to analyze the competencies teachers need to acquire.",
    "The TPACK framework, as elucidated by Koehler et al. (2013), offers a comprehensive view of the knowledge systems essential for effective STEM teaching.",
    "This framework categorizes teacher knowledge into seven components: content, technology, and pedagogy (Yildiz Durak et al. 2023).",
    "Understanding each element, from subject matter to integrating modern technologies in teaching, provides a nuanced perspective on the competencies required for STEM education.",
    "Unlike adult learning theory, which focuses on how teachers learn, TPACK focuses on what teachers need to know to integrate technology into STEM education effectively."
  ]
}